gomodel:SYNGO_2769  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.5: \"Neurexin promotes coaggregation of NL3 with glutamatergic and GABAergic postsynaptic scaffolds.\"\n\nNote: this data is correlational in nature. The annotation relies on the known ability of neurexin-1 to induce clustering and postsynaptic differentiation via neuroligins.. Experimental description: - \"Subcellular fractionation from adult rat brain was performed as previously described (Carlin et al., 1980), with minor modifications. Briefly, brains from three adult male rats were homogenized\"\n- \"Dissociated hippocampal cultures were prepared from embryonic day 18 (E18) rats.\"" ;
